  "chapter": {
    "number": 6,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Carry One Another’s Burdens"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Brothers, if someone is caught in a trespass, you who are spiritual should restore him with a spirit of gentleness. But watch yourself, or you also may be tempted."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "Carry one another’s burdens, and in this way you will fulfill the law of Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "If anyone thinks he is something when he is nothing, he deceives himself."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "Each one should test his own work. Then he will have reason to boast in himself alone, and not in someone else."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "For each one should carry his own load."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "Nevertheless, the one who receives instruction in the word must share in all good things with his instructor."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "Do not be deceived: God is not to be mocked. Whatever a man sows, he will reap in return."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "The one who sows to please his flesh, from the flesh will reap destruction; but the one who sows to please the Spirit, from the Spirit will reap eternal life."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "Let us not grow weary in well-doing, for in due time we will reap a harvest if we do not give up."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "Therefore, as we have opportunity, let us do good to everyone, and especially to the family of faith."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Final Warnings and Blessings"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "See what large letters I am using to write to you with my own hand!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "Those who want to make a good impression outwardly are trying to compel you to be circumcised. They only do this to avoid persecution for the cross of Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "For the circumcised do not even keep the law themselves, yet they want you to be circumcised that they may boast in your flesh."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "But as for me, may I never boast, except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, through which",
          {
            "noteId": 2110
          },
          "the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "For neither circumcision nor uncircumcision means anything. What counts is a new creation."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "Peace and mercy to all who walk by this rule, even to the Israel of God."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "From now on let no one cause me trouble, for I bear on my body the marks of Jesus."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit, brothers.",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "Amen."
        ]
      }
    ],
